[SN]TITLE[SN]
Woman pedestrian hit by car at Clarence Place, Newport

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A pedestrian has been airlifted to hospital after being hit by a car in Newport.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Gwent Police said the woman had sustained "life-threatening injuries" in the crash involving a silver Ford Focus at Clarence Place at 13:30 GMT on Thursday.
Town Bridge has been shut in both directions and diversions are in place.
Drivers have been advised to avoid the area due to heavy traffic.
